3:["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Phemex calculates JTO/USDT funding rates every 8 hours at 00:00, 08:00, and 16:00 UTC using the premium/discount between perpetual and spot prices. The funding rate is capped at ±0.75% per interval to prevent extreme payments. Long positions pay funding when rates are positive, while short positions receive payments, with settlements occurring automatically in your USDT margin balance."}]
4:["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":["Why ","JTO","/","USDT","?"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"JTO's connection to Solana's liquid staking ecosystem creates distinct funding patterns driven by SOL network activity and DeFi yield farming cycles. The token's relatively recent listing and smaller market cap on Phemex can generate funding rate inefficiencies during periods of asymmetric positioning."}]]}]
5:["$","section","0",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"JTO Funding Rate Patterns"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"JTO funding rates on Phemex typically correlate with broader Solana DeFi sentiment and liquid staking demand cycles. During SOL network upgrades or high staking yields, JTO often experiences positive funding as traders go long to capture ecosystem growth. The token shows heightened volatility around Jito protocol updates and validator reward distributions. Weekend periods frequently see reduced funding rate volatility due to lower institutional participation in this smaller-cap DeFi token."}]]}]
6:["$","section","1",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Arbitrage Opportunities"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Phemex's lower liquidity for JTO compared to major exchanges creates funding rate arbitrage opportunities, particularly during Asian trading hours when the Singapore-based platform sees peak activity. Cross-exchange arbitrage between Phemex and Binance often emerges when Solana ecosystem news drives asymmetric positioning. The 0.01% maker fee structure makes it cost-effective to maintain delta-neutral positions for funding collection. Monitor funding rates against OKX and Bybit for the most profitable arbitrage setups."}]]}]
7:["$","section","2",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Risk Considerations"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"JTO's smaller trading volume on Phemex increases slippage risk during volatile periods, especially around Solana network events or major DeFi protocol announcements. The token's correlation with SOL price movements can create unexpected P&L swings in funding strategies. Phemex's liquidity gaps during low-volume periods may result in wider bid-ask spreads, impacting entry and exit execution. Position sizing should account for the platform's smaller user base and potential for sudden liquidity dry-ups during market stress."}]]}]
8:["$","$Ld",null,{"items":[{"question":"What are typical JTO funding rates on Phemex?","answer":"JTO funding rates on Phemex typically range from -0.1% to +0.3% per 8-hour period, with higher positive rates during Solana ecosystem rallies. Rates tend to be more volatile than major tokens due to smaller positioning size and lower liquidity."},{"question":"How does JTO funding compare across exchanges?","answer":"Phemex often shows higher funding rate spreads for JTO compared to Binance or OKX due to its smaller market share and specialized derivatives focus. This creates arbitrage opportunities but requires careful liquidity management."},{"question":"When are JTO funding payments most profitable on Phemex?","answer":"JTO funding collection is typically most profitable during Solana ecosystem events, validator reward distributions, or liquid staking yield changes when positioning becomes skewed. Monitor correlations with SOL price and staking APY changes."},{"question":"What's the minimum position size for JTO funding strategies?","answer":"Phemex requires a minimum of 1 JTO for perpetual positions, but effective funding strategies typically start around 100+ JTO to overcome trading fees and potential slippage in this smaller liquidity environment."}]}]
